This directory contains a test generator which is capable of generating
pseudo-directed random tests using similar structure as the benchmark program

To run this test generator, 
First, 

sh link.sh
make clean; make OS=LINUX DEC_DATATYPE=$DEC_DATATYPE WIDTH=$BITWIDTH

Then followed by

./LINUX.Banking.TestGen.DEC64 $OUTPUT_FILE $MAX_ACCT $MAX_TX $MIN_TX $NO_DAYS

$OUTPUT_FILE is the output filename
$MAX_ACCT is the maximum number of accounts (in all categories) that can be
active at any given day
$MAX_TX is the maximum transaction per day
$MIN_TX is the minimum transaction per day
$NO_DAYS is the number of days' transaction that should be generated

When you run this program, it will generate the ascii version of this file called 
$OUTPUT_FILE.txt and located in the ascii/ folder. It will also generate a binary 
version of it called $OUTPUT_FILE.$DEC_DATATYPE in the bin/ directory. 
Use the binary file for the benchmark simulation and ascii output file
for your reference.
